$ VIM: src/window.c

{ win_alloc()

  Allocates a new window structure.

  If the new window is not `hidden`, the window is linked into the window list.

}
{ win_alloc_first() #vim-src-window-win_alloc_first

 `win_alloc_first` allocates the first → development/vim/editing/windows[window] and puts an empty → development/vim/editing/buffers[buffer] into it.

  Vim won't start up if this function fails.

}
